    "comment": "Rationale: Figure 3a: Immunofluorescence labeling for LAMP5 and GAD65 proteins demonstrates co-labelling in GABAergic axon terminals in the globus pallidus. However, LAMP5 immunoreactivity never overlaps with vGLUT1, thus it is absent from glutamatergic synapses.\n\nFigure 3d: Electron microscopy immunogold labeling showed gold particles linked to the LAMP5 antibody were always associated with the typical synapses that granule neurons in the olfactory bulb form on the apical dendrites of mitral cells.\n\nFigure 4a,b: confocal imaging of immunofluorescence labeling for LAMP5 and VGAT showed strong co-localization\n\nFigure 4c: synaptic vesicles immunoisolated using a VGAT antibody showed LAMP5 is specifically found in the VGAT positive fraction.\n\nauthors conclude:\n\"these data suggest that LAMP5 is expressed in subpopulations of GABAergic neurons where it largely co-localizes in synaptic vesicles with VGAT\". Experimental description: \"LAMP5 conditional mutant mice were generated by the KO-KI Booster platform, CIPHE, Marseille...\" (p.2/19)\n\nantibody:\nLAMP5 antibody described in PMID:21642595\nnote that the antibody was validated using knockout mice in Figure 2",
